This paper deals with natural language processing and dialogue systems, which are typically covered under the Computer Science sub-category of Computation and Language (cs.CL). The paper proposes a new model for resolving ellipsis and co-reference in dialogue, which involves generating missing or referred expressions from the context. This task involves machine learning and artificial intelligence techniques, which are covered under the sub-categories of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG). The paper also proposes a multi-task learning framework for integrating the GECOR model into an end-to-end task-oriented dialogue system, which involves optimization and decision-making, covered under the sub-categories of Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) and Systems and Control (cs.SD).
